==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Latching
<hw>Latch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A loop or eye
formed on the head rope of a bonnet, by which it is attached to the foot
of a sail; -- called also <altname>latch</altname> and
<altname>lasket</altname>.</def> <mark>[Usually in pl.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Latchkey</ent>⟦br⟧
